Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.84,0:03:39.02,Header,,0,0,0,,Note: 771 BC – 476 BC
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.84,0:03:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In the times of Spring and Autumn,\Nfive hegemons strove for supremacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.22,0:03:42.73,Header,,0,0,0,,Note: 475 BC – 221 BC
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.22,0:03:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,During the Warring States period,\Nseven kingdoms clashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.35,0:03:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,After five centuries of strife, they were united under Qín.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.04,0:03:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,After the Qín fell,\Ntwo rival nations arose: Chǔ and Hàn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.98,0:03:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, all were once again\Nunited under the Hàn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.71,0:04:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 2nd year of Zhānghe\Nof the Eastern Hàn dynasty,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.71,0:04:07.31,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: 88 AD
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.62,0:04:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the ten-year-old Emperor Hé of Hàn\Nascended the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.71,0:04:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,With the help of eunuchs, he was able\Nto depose Empress Dowager Dòu
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.02,0:04:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,along with her elder brother,\NGeneralissimo Dòu Xiàn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.53,0:04:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Eunuchs became a part of government function,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.20,0:04:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and their domination marked the\Nbeginning of the end for the Hàn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.37,0:04:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.13,0:04:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.00,0:04:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live His Majesty!
