Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.98,0:05:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Shāng of Hàn,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.55,0:05:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Ān,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.86,0:05:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Shùn,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.51,0:05:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Chōng,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.68,0:05:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Zhì,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.02,0:05:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Huán and Emperor Líng.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.96,0:05:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Emperors' deposition became constant \Nand the court's power withered away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.82,0:05:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, local gentry became despots, extorting the people
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.66,0:05:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and annexing land as natural\Ndisasters ravaged the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.31,0:05:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The common people were on a knife's edge, \Nliving in torment by desolation and starvation.
